# Caddy reverse proxy.

# Base domain for the service hostnames (music.$DOMAIN, photos.$DOMAIN, ...).
# Falls back to localhost so the stack still parses before you set it; for
# real use point it at a domain you control. The shared root .env also has a
# DOMAIN — set it there and it flows through ./scripts/manage.sh.
DOMAIN=example.com

# Where Caddy proxies to. Defaults to the host gateway so it can reach each
# service's published port. If host.containers.internal doesn't resolve in
# your podman setup, set this to the server's LAN IP, e.g. 192.168.1.50.
# UPSTREAM_HOST=192.168.1.50

# Only needed to switch the Caddyfile (tls) snippet to the Cloudflare DNS
# challenge for publicly-trusted certs. Create a scoped API token with
# Zone:Read + DNS:Edit for your zone. Leave blank for the default internal CA.
# CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN=
